<h2 class="underline">Krita Comments</h2>
<div class="discussionApp">
<div class="threadTable row post-5003 threadHeader half-gutters" id="post-3456">
<div class="imageHolder col-xs-1 hidden-xs" style="vertical-align: top">
<span style="background-color: #CB5E08" class="imageHolder profile-image pull-left">H</span>
</div>
<div class="col-xs-11">
<div class="threadMetaWrapper meta">
<span class="threadMeta">
Comment by
<a data-container="body" data-placement="bottom" data-toggle="popover-ajax" data-url="/user/homeyd5/modal" itemProp="Name" rel="nofollow" tabindex="0">HomeyD5</a>
</span>
<div class="threadMeta">
about
<a class='mainApp' href='/software/krita/'>Krita</a>
<span title="A review or comment" class="ThreadReview clear small-icon"></span>
&middot; <span> <span title='2011-06-29 2:20:01 PM'>Jun 2011</span></span>
&middot;
<span data-helpful-threadid="3456" class="emotion emotion-positive forum-hover helpful-comment"><i class="icon-thumbs-up-alt"></i>Helpful</span>
<span data-helpful-threadid="3456" class="emotion emotion-negative forum-hover not-helpful-comment"><i class="icon-thumbs-down-alt"></i>Not helpful</span>
<span class="emotion emotion-positive helpful-comment forum-hover-hide"><i class="icon-thumbs-up-alt"></i>5 Helpful</span>
<span data-spam-threadid="3456" class="meta pull-right forum-hover report-spam"><i class="icon-cancel-circled"></i>Report as spam</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class="do-not-break forumText wmd">
<p>Krita is geared more towa artists rather than photographers, and has a toolset which reflects that. While a number of photography-specific tools are missing, Krita can still be a very powerful photo editor when suplemented by another program to handle the basic raw conversion and curve editing. The fact that Krita supports deep color gives it a big advantage over GIMP, at least until the next full version release of GIMP.</p>
</div>
<div class="meta">
<span data-toggle="modal" data-target="#loginDialog" data-redirecturl="/software/krita/" class="reply meta notloggedin"><span class="link-color">reply</span></span>
